For every component of the object, give in this order
- the NAME of TYPE POINT LIGNE SURFACE VOLUME or OBJET
  (This NAME can be REDUCED to its FIRST LETTER)
-the NAME of the POINT LINE SURFACE VOLUME or OBJET 

Example :
5;   O; O3;  VOLUME; V1;  SURFACE; S7;  L; L5;  POINT; P1;
L'OBJET is composed of 5 PLSVO, one of each type.

Example in 3D:       
5; { OBJETS PARTIES DE L OBJET }
 JAW; {NAME DE L'OBJET}
 0;   {CLASSICAL 2D or 3D }
 5;   {NBDOBJ NUMBER of POINTS LINES SURFACES VOLUMES OBJECTS of the OBJECT}
 V; MECHANICAL_PIECE; {NTYOBJ(1..NBDOBJ) 'TYPE of PLSVO NAME and PLSVO NAME}
 S; RIGHT_WASHER;
 S; LEFT_WASHER;
 S; CYLINDER_WITH_FORCE;
 S; RAIL_FIXED;
 @;
7; { INTERPOLATION DEFINITION of MESH NODES}
 JAW; 4; { LAGRANGE of DEGREE 2 }
@;

Example in axisymmetric:
5;{ OBJECTS components of the OBJECT }
 WATER_CASTLE;  0; {classic solution 2D or 3D with renumbering}
 5; { number of Points Lines Surfaces Volumes Objects of the object }
 SURFACE; GROUND;
 SURFACE; CONCRETE;
 LIGNE;   D2E2;
 L; D1D2;
 L; DISPLNULL;
@;
7; { Interpolation }
 WATER_CASTLE;
 2; {AXISYMETRIC LAGRANGE DEGREE 2}
@;
